[
    {
        "text": "Let's look at some different",
        "start": 0.16,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "ways to use 'like' in British English.",
        "start": 1.28,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "We can use 'like' as an active verb",
        "start": 4.0,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "which means 'to feel positive about'.",
        "start": 6.64,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "'I like my dad - he's great.'",
        "start": 9.12,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "We can also use 'to be like'.",
        "start": 11.36,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "This means the same as 'similar'.",
        "start": 14.88,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "'I am like my dad because we",
        "start": 17.04,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "both have brown hair.'",
        "start": 19.68,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "'Like' can also mean 'such as'.",
        "start": 21.12,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "'My dad enjoys many sports, like football.'",
        "start": 24.08,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, we can use the expression",
        "start": 27.68,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "'like, like' to say that two",
        "start": 30.16,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "family members are the same.",
        "start": 32.8,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "'Like mother, like daughter'",
        "start": 34.8,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "or 'like father, like son'.",
        "start": 37.2,
        "duration": 3.0
    }
]